CSS short hand properties are those properties that let you set the values of multiple other CSS properties simultaneously
in a sinle line which is a more compact way of writing CSS.
example
container {
    border-width 1px;
    border-style solid;
    border-color #000;
}
Shorthand could border
container{
    border: 1px solid #000
}
It is the shortest way of writing CSS rules or properties.
WHERE ELSE CAN WE USE THE SHORTHANDS
The CSS background
Which is used to set the background of a web page.
For example:
Container{
    background -color: #000;
    background-image: url [sample jpeg];
    background-repeat: no repeat;
    background-position: top right;
}
    The shorthand will be;
   Container{
    background:#000  url(sample jpeg) no repeat top right; each value seperated by a space.
   }
THE FONT is another property
for example,
Container{
    font-size: large;
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 100;
}
Short hand example
Container{
    font:large arial,helvetica,sans-serif italic 100;
}
The ordered and unordered list are used when displaying a list of information in an html document.
ordered list [ol] and unordered list [ul]
ol is displayed using numbers
ul is dislplayed using bullets

Container{
    list-style: armenian;
    list-style-position: unset;
    list-style-image: none;
}
The short hand would be 
Container{
    list-style: armenian unset none;
}
The CSS outline property are used to add an outline to different elements in a web page.
For example
Container{
    outline-offset: 0cap;
    outline-color: #000;
    outline-width: 0cap;
}
The shorthand would be 
Container{
    outline: 0cap  #000 0cap;
}
Shorthand versions of margin and padding work similarly
Margin allows 1, 2, 3 or 4 values 
For example:
Container{
    margin-top 10px;
    margin-right 5px;
    margin-bottom 10px;
    margin-left 5px;
}
The shorthand would be 
Container{
    margin: 10px 5px 10px 5px;
}
Padding is similar to the above.
  